## Expo Commands Reference

### Development Server

```powershell
# Start Metro bundler (interactive menu)
npm start

# Start and immediately open Android
npm run android

# Start for web only
npm run web

# Clear Metro cache
npx expo start --clear

# Start on specific port
npx expo start --port 8082
```

### Installing Packages

```powershell
# ✅ GOOD: Expo packages (use expo install)
npx expo install expo-sqlite
npx expo install expo-router
npx expo install expo-secure-store
npx expo install expo-file-system
npx expo install expo-image-picker

# ✅ GOOD: Standard npm packages
npm install firebase
npm install uuid
npm install @types/uuid

# ❌ BAD: Don't use expo install for non-Expo packages
# npx expo install uuid  # Wrong!
```

### Building & Testing

```powershell
# Generate native folders (android/ios) - rarely needed
npx expo prebuild

# Run TypeScript type checking
npx tsc --noEmit

# Run linter
npm run lint

# Clear all caches
npx expo start --clear
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force node_modules
Remove-Item package-lock.json
npm install
```

