## Navigation with Expo Router

### File-Based Routing

Expo Router uses file structure for navigation:

```
app/
├── _layout.tsx              # Root layout
├── index.tsx                # Route: / (home)
├── (tabs)/                  # Tab group
│   ├── _layout.tsx          # Tabs layout
│   ├── index.tsx            # Route: /(tabs)/ (home tab)
│   └── budget.tsx           # Route: /(tabs)/budget
├── transaction/[id].tsx     # Route: /transaction/:id (dynamic)
└── +not-found.tsx           # 404 fallback
```

### Navigation Examples

```typescript
import { router, Link } from 'expo-router';

// Navigate programmatically
router.push('/transaction/123');
router.replace('/login');
router.back();

// Link component
<Link href="/transaction/123">View Transaction</Link>
<Link href={{ pathname: '/transaction/[id]', params: { id: '123' } }}>
  View Transaction
</Link>
```

